                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27068",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There was regression here:\nWhat goes wrong here is that an extra < is rendered.\n{code}\n        foreach ($items as $item) {\n            if (!is_array($item)) {\n                if ($escape) {\n                    $item = $this->view->escape($item);\n                }\n                $list .= '<li>' . $item . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n            } else {\n                if (5 < strlen($list)) {\n                    $list = substr($list, 0, strlen($list) - 5)\n                     . $this->htmlList($item, $ordered, $attribs, $escape) . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n                } else {\n                    $list .= '<li>' . $this->htmlList($item, $ordered, $attribs, $escape) . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n{code}\nI changed it to: (note the 6 instead of 5)\n{code}\n        foreach ($items as $item) {\n            if (!is_array($item)) {\n                if ($escape) {\n                    $item = $this->view->escape($item);\n                }\n                $list .= '<li>' . $item . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n            } else {\n                if (5 < strlen($list)) {\n                    $list = substr($list, 0, strlen($list) - 6)\n                     . $this->htmlList($item, $ordered, $attribs, $escape) . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n                } else {\n                    $list .= '<li>' . $this->htmlList($item, $ordered, $attribs, $escape) . '<\/li>' . self::EOL;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n{code}\n\nBecause this is so obvious and so minor I have decided not to create an extra issue, but commit it referring to this issue.",
